Whisk dressing ingredients in medium bowl until creamy. Cut beef tenderloin tips into 1- by 1/2-inch pieces. Heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add 1/2 of beef; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until outside surface of beef is no longer pink. Remove beef with slotted spoon and reserve. Repeat with remaining beef. Season with salt and pepper. In large bowl, toss greens with 1/2 cup dressing; place on platter. Top with beef and croutons. Serve with remaining dressing.